            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Using urxvt here, the cursor is a block when I'm in normal mode, and a caret when in insert mode (seems to be the default now).\r\n\r\nTo spot the cursor easily I use `:set cursorline` & `set cursorcolumn` that makes a cross on the screen, with the cursor at the intersection.\r\n\r\nExample in Insert mode:\r\n![spot_cursor](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9730330/32418417-d380dd0e-c269-11e7-82ba-2131568cdce9.png)\r\n\r\nThis way it's pretty easy to spot the cursor when you're looking for it, does this help?\r\n\r\nEdit:\r\nI don't know if it's the terminal that does this, but I can clearly see the character under the cursor:\r\n![spot_cursor](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/9730330/32418454-74bfcc48-c26a-11e7-9692-9da9436957e3.png)\r\n",
