            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "One flaw of using `set cursorcolumn` for the purposes of locating your cursor, is that it doesn't work well on lines that are visually wrapped (columns above and below will only be highlighted if they also wrap to the degree that the current cursor position does).\r\n\r\nThat may actually be a nice neovim enhancement.  A new option (`set virtualcursorcolumn`?) which will always provide a vertical indicator of position, irrespective of wrapping.",
