            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Hi @justinmk, I'm referring to the feature where most of the TE program will handle the reverse color of the box (or block) cursor. More specifically, the iTerm2 has the feature to automatically reverse the font color under the box cursor such that one can spot the character at the cursor's position. I've used other modern TE programs like those in Gnome and KDE, but never notice any color issue with the box cursor. So I guess this is only an issue affecting Windows users? Or is there any setting in the Windows cmd.exe program that can be turned on?",
            "created_at": "2019-11-07T19:18:09Z",
